#: ../../authentication_authorization/roles.rst:3
msgid "Roles"
msgstr "Roller"

#: ../../authentication_authorization/roles.rst:5
msgid ""
"Role management is done in the administration page at **Authentication "
"and Authorization > Roles**"
msgstr ""
"Hantering av roller görs på administrationssidan under **Autentisiering "
"och Auktorisering > Roller**"

#: ../../authentication_authorization/roles.rst:10
msgid ""
"Permissions are required for managing roles. :ref:`More info "
"<role_permissions>`"
msgstr ""
"Rättigheter krävs för att hantera roller. :ref:`Mer info "
"<role_permissions>`"

#: ../../authentication_authorization/roles.rst:15
msgid "Creating roles"
msgstr "Skapa roller"

#: ../../authentication_authorization/roles.rst:17
msgid ""
"To create a new role, click ``ADD ROLE`` in the top-right corner. On the "
"new page, give the role a **unique** name and add one or more permissions"
" to it. Click ``SAVE`` when done."
msgstr ""

#: ../../authentication_authorization/roles.rst:24
msgid "Assigning roles"
msgstr "Tilldela roller"

#: ../../authentication_authorization/roles.rst:26
msgid ""
"To assign a role to a user, go to the user at **Authentication and "
"Authorization > Users**. Click on the user and scroll down to ``ASSIGNED "
"ROLES``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../authentication_authorization/roles.rst:30
msgid ""
"Here you can add one more roles to the groups that the user is a member "
"of. You can also give the membership an optional expiration date."
msgstr ""
